    "media:imagetext": "2/300\nJOHN HINDE\nORIGINA\nIRELAND\nPrinted\nand Published\nTERMINAL\n_BUILDING,\nCORK\nAIRPORT,\nIRELAND: Cork Airport was opened in October 1961\nand established direct connections with the South of\nIreland and Dublin, Western England, London and the\nContinent. It stands on 500 acres with two runways,\nthe larger measuring 6,000 feet capable of handling\njets and the other measuring 4,300 feet. The 80 ft.\nhigh control tower dominates the airport. In it is housed\nevery modern electronic aid for aviation.\nby John Hinde Limited, Cabinteely, Co. Dublin, Irish Republic.\n2015,166.1895",
